HEADWORD: myxedema
<hw>myxedema</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A pathological
condition due to severe hyperthyroidism, marked by dry skin and
swellings around lips and nose as well as mental and physical
deterioration.</def> <altsp>[Also spelled
<asp>myxoedema</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Myxine</ent>⟦br⟧
